        <bioghist id="ref3">
            <head>Biographical note</head>
            <p>Edith Horton lived on Macon Street in Brooklyn and was Principal of P.S. 7 in Brooklyn.</p>
        </bioghist>
        <scopecontent id="ref2">
            <head>Scope and Contents note</head>
            <p>The collection includes correspondence from the New York City Department of Education to Edith Horton concerning contributions for the M. Samuel Stern Memorial Fund, which she chaired; a loyalty certificate; a deed between Alice Stiles and Frank Swimm for land in the city of Brooklyn; a teaching certificate for Edith Horton; and a printed poem with a handwritten message on the back.</p>
        </scopecontent>
